interview Questions asked in Databricks for Senior Technical Data Engineer role

Interview Rounds:

6 rounds of interview (3 Tech rounds + Live Coding Round + Executive Round + Director Round)

Focus areas:

- Spark internals (DAGs, shuffles, executors, partitions)
- Issue Identification (Spark UI, logs, and metrics)
- Databricks architecture
- Practical Support Scenarios

1) Project & Architecture

* Explain your end-to-end project architecture using Databricks
* Describe Medallion Architecture (Bronze → Silver → Gold)
* Clearly explain data flow and design decisions

2) Spark Internals

* Driver vs Executor roles 
* Execution flow: Jobs -> Stages -> Tasks 
* DAG creation and task execution 
* Memory management and JVM GC behaviour 
* Interpret GC logs and identify memory pressure issues 

3) Performance Tuning & Troubleshooting

* Data skew & shuffle handling 
* Broadcast joins vs shuffle joins 
* Handling OOM (Out Of Memory) errors 
* Spark UI (Jobs, Stages, SQL tabs) 
* Logs, metrics 
* Cache vs Broadcast 
* UDF vs native functions (performance impact) 

4) Spark Structured Streaming

* Checkpointing (offsets, state, metadata) 
* Watermarking & late data handling 
* State management across micro-batches 
* Debug issues (OOM errors, Skewed partitions, Slow streaming jobs)

5) Delta Lake & File Formats

* ACID transactions 
* delta_log metadata 
* Time travel & retention 
* Optimistic concurrency control
* Operations (Merge, Incremental loads, Vacuum & file cleanup)
* Compare Parquet vs Avro vs Delta vs Iceberg

6) SQL & Analytical Processing

* FROM -> JOIN -> WHERE -> GROUP BY -> HAVING -> SELECT -> ORDER BY
* Joins & aggregations
* Window/analytical functions

7) Data Modeling & File Design

* Row vs Columnar formats (Parquet, ORC, Avro)
* Best practices for Partitioning & bucketing

8) Databricks Platform & Cluster Management

* Cluster types (job vs all-purpose)
* Autoscaling & VM sizing
* Driver vs Worker nodes
* Managed vs External tables
* Init scripts

9) Practical Scenarios (Most Important)

* How do you Break down pipeline into Jobs -> Stages -> Tasks 
* How to Debug slow Spark jobs using Spark UI
* Ways to handle Data skew, OOM errors and Streaming failures
* Brief about Spark 3.0 features (Adaptive Query Execution and Auto skew handling)
